---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Advanced Rider — TT Motorcycle School"
  description="Advanced motorcycle rider training in Sussex with TT Motorcycle School. IAM and RoSPA-aligned coaching to improve your skills, safety and confidence."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Advanced Riding</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Enhanced Rider Scheme</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        Take your riding to the next level with the DVSA Enhanced Rider Scheme —
        gain a respected certificate, ride with greater confidence, and unlock
        insurance discounts with up to 30 providers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Enhanced Rider Scheme (ERS)</h2>
        <p>
          For all category A and A2 riders who wish to take it to the next step
          and gain the much respected Enhanced Rider Scheme (ERS) certificate —
          we can fulfil this dream.
        </p>
        <p>
          Gaining the ERS certificate will not only make you a more skilful and
          confident rider but you may benefit from insurance discounts from
          almost 30 different insurance companies, which include some of the
          largest names in Motorcycle Insurance — such as Carole Nash and
          Devitts.
        </p>

        <h2>Our ERS Training</h2>
        <p>
          Our ERS training is carried out by our DVSA Approved Post-Test
          Motorcycle Trainer. Courses are for a minimum of one day at <strong
            >£200 per day</strong
          >. If you book with a friend the total fee is <strong>£320</strong> — a
          saving of £80 between you and far less than the daily training rate! So
          grab a motorcycling buddy and <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>!
        </p>

        <h2>What You'll Receive</h2>
        <p>
          Once you've completed your training you will receive a report and a
          <strong
            >'DVSA Certificate of Competence – Enhanced Rider Bonus'</strong
          >, which then qualifies you for the insurance discount.
        </p>

        <h2>Ready to Book?</h2>
        <p>
          If you wish to know more or indeed book a course please
          <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> so we can talk you through the process
          and discuss dates.
        </p>

        <div style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">
          <CTAButton
            href="/contact/"
            label="Get in Touch"
            variant="accent"
            size="md"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar__card sidebar__card--plain">
          <h3 class="sidebar__title">Useful Links</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar__links">
            <li><a href="/OneToOneTraining/">One-to-One Training</a></li>
            <li><a href="/bespoke-refresher/">Bespoke & Refresher</a></li>
            <li><a href="/prices/">Pricing</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact/">Contact Us</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    }
  }

  .sidebar__card {
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .sidebar__card--plain {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .sidebar__title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .sidebar__links {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .sidebar__links a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .sidebar__links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
